slides.title: European Community Networks
slides.text:
Here is the Web mapping of European Community Networks (CNs).

It is comprised of four main groups who have strong online ties, and organized around leading CNs in Germany, Spain, France and the Czech Republic. In between are other CNs from Italy, Greece, Hungaria, the UK, etc.

The map was made using Hyphe, a Web crawling and curating tool, which explore the hyperlinks between websites  (http://hyphe.medialab.sciences-po.fr/).

slides.title: Other CNs
slides.text: Other CNs have an intermediary position in this online map.

slides.title: Isolated nodes
slides.text: Some isolated islands come up in the graph such as this one, which connects Danish CNs (GrenaaS.net being of the wrong color here)

slides.title: Other isolated nodes
slides.text: These nodes are not connected either because the design they use prevents the crawler from exploring their hyperlinks, or because the website itself does not link to other web entities in our corpus.

slides.title: European Community Networks
slides.text: Youn can use the legend on the bottom-left corner and explore the network by zooming in and out.
